#: ../../contributing.rst:360 11059a79f2524fd1bde0e9ad04b48321
msgid "Whiskers"
msgstr ""

#: ../../contributing.rst:362 1a28d7ced97d4fef9ac91e63640f1ccd
msgid "*Whiskers* is a string templating system similar to `Mustache <https://mustache.github.io>`_. It is used by the compiler in various places to aid readability, and thus maintainability and verifiability, of the code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../contributing.rst:365 e0ffabf76a384c5d91eb30de04d6bcaa
msgid "The syntax comes with a substantial difference to Mustache. The template markers ``{{`` and ``}}`` are replaced by ``<`` and ``>`` in order to aid parsing and avoid conflicts with :ref:`yul` (The symbols ``<`` and ``>`` are invalid in inline assembly, while ``{`` and ``}`` are used to delimit blocks). Another limitation is that lists are only resolved one depth and they do not recurse. This may change in the future."
msgstr ""

#: ../../contributing.rst:370 e145aaf348d74999a6e7cedab77feb78
msgid "A rough specification is the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../contributing.rst:372 cadfab58810f4c48a4ae4c9952f16403
msgid "Any occurrence of ``<name>`` is replaced by the string-value of the supplied variable ``name`` without any escaping and without iterated replacements. An area can be delimited by ``<#name>...</name>``. It is replaced by as many concatenations of its contents as there were sets of variables supplied to the template system, each time replacing any ``<inner>`` items by their respective value. Top-level variables can also be used inside such areas."
msgstr ""

#: ../../contributing.rst:378 3f2416da5fb3408cb1ff0b2aff8b0f29
msgid "There are also conditionals of the form ``<?name>...<!name>...</name>``, where template replacements continue recursively either in the first or the second segment depending on the value of the boolean parameter ``name``. If ``<?+name>...<!+name>...</+name>`` is used, then the check is whether the string parameter ``name`` is non-empty."
msgstr ""

